# Project Structure

This monorepo is organized into:

- `packages/`: shared libraries and feature modules (e.g., `packages/backend`, `packages/commons`, `packages/web-ui`, `packages/frontend`).

## Modular structure

Across apps and packages, feature areas live under `src/modules/<feature>/`. Each module follows consistent file conventions to keep responsibilities separated.

### Module file types (brief)

- `.constants.ts`: central constants and configuration flags for the module. 
- `.schema.ts`: validation and data contracts (e.g., Zod schemas) and derived TypeScript types.
- `.db.ts`: database layer definitions for the module (tables/models, queries, helpers).
- `.repository.ts`: data access layer encapsulating persistence operations behind an interface.
- `.service.ts`: business logic orchestrating repositories and cross-module rules.
- `.trpc.ts`: tRPC routers/procedures exposing the module's type-safe API surface.


### UI folders

- `components/`: presentational and composite UI pieces scoped to the module/package (frontend-only).
- `hooks/`: reusable React hooks encapsulating client-side state/effects for the module (frontend-only).

